history.content:
Hi everyone,

One of my friends -- who was a triple major in EECS/DS/Econ and now a EECS Masters candidate and a Tesla engineer -- just started a Discord group focused on technical analysis and principles of trading. He's been trading for seven years now and is very passionate in sharing what he learned and his experiences during this turbulent time.

We have a lot of resources in the Discord group including (but not limited to): principles of a good trader, educational materials focused on trading, weekly zoom seminars, and bots that deliver news and market information such as big volume trades and critical points to help guide you along your trading path. There will also be nightly economic outlook and market analysis as well as live trading during the day. Also, there are no required commmitments.

Thank you! Hope to see you there.

https://discordapp.com/invite/JuyWjPC

We also have a Facebook group where daily analysis will be posted there. The name is "CAL-TRADING". However, most of the resources we think are most useful and unique will be inside our Discord channels.

Thank you for your attention!
